# Markdown Docs Rule

When editing markdown docs:

- Keep policy text aligned with canonical project sources.
- Use normative language consistently (`must`, `should`, `may`).
- Keep guidance actionable and concise.
- Avoid duplicating nearby docs; prefer links to canonical references.
- If policy changes (not only wording), update all affected docs in the same PR.
- Apply the same standards to man-page markdown sources under `docs/docs/**/man/*.md` and `docs/docs/flags/*.md`.
